msgid "The `#[slot]` macro annotates a plain Rust struct as component slot:"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/09_component_children.md:112
msgid ""
"// A simple struct annotated with `#[slot]`,\n"
"// which expects children\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/09_component_children.md:120
msgid "This slot can be used as a prop in a component:"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/09_component_children.md:125
msgid "// Component slot, should be passed through the <Then slot> syntax\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/09_component_children.md:138
msgid ""
"Now, the `If` component expects a child of type `Then`. You would need to "
"annotate the used slot with `slot:<prop_name>`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/09_component_children.md:142
msgid "// The `If` component always expects a `Then` child for `then_slot`\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/view/09_component_children.md:148
msgid ""
"Specifying `slot` without a name will default the chosen slot as the snake "
"case version of the struct name. So in this case `<Then slot>` would be "
"equivalent to `<Then slot:then>`."
msgstr ""

#: src/view/09_component_children.md:150
msgid ""
"For the complete example, see [slots examples](https://github.com/leptos-rs/"
"leptos/tree/main/examples/slots)."
msgstr ""

